node.text:
Presented on Coach TV, it’s the story of our new Winter Collection (looks, roller skates and snow included). #COACH秀场直击 #CoachNY

Coach Creative Director: @stuartvevers
Stylist: #OlivierRizzo
Set & Film Designer: @stefanbeckman
Film Editor: #GregEmetaz
Music: #SteveMackey
With Thanks To: @ashleybrokaw, @guidopalau and @patmcgrathreal
Vignette Director: @dani_aphrodite
Hot 41 Countdown Director: @jasonbergh
House of Coach Writers: #AmberSchaefer and @yonilotan

node.text: A Live look at how Malaysian-born artist and model Sheena Liam (@times.new.romance) brings her embroidery to life. On why she’s proud to be a Coach collaborator: “Coach has always been bold, authentic and unapologetic when it comes to the art they feature in their collections. This resonates with me. Embroidery can be a quiet tool of resistance.” Watch here on IGTV. #CoachNY

node.text:
Did you miss the live broadcast of Coach Forever Season Two? Shown on “Coach TV,” it is the story of our Fall 2021 Collection and made in collaboration with #JuergenTeller and the #CoachFamily; with pre-show vignettes by #FrancesFrances. Watch the re-run here.

Coach Creative Director: @stuartvevers 
Coach Forever Photographer and Director: #JuergenTeller 
Coach Forever Creative Partner to Juergen Teller: @doviledrizyte 
Coach Forever Music: “Thinking About Your Love” by Skipworth & Turner
Stylist: #OlivierRizzo
With Thanks To: @ashleybrokaw, @guidopalau and @patmcgrathreal
Pre-Show Vignette Writer and Director: #FrancesFrances 
Additional Pre-Show Entertainment Director: @dani_aphrodite, plus @cake_films and @zuekster 
#CoachNY

One that has value and has a voice." Listen now and make sure your voice is heard in this election. #CoachNY

node.text: Singer and actress #JackieCruz spoke with President and CEO of @VotoLatino, #MariaTeresaKumar about these voting topics and more. “Democracy thrives when we all participate,” said Maria. “Our job is to make a date with it: to love it and to nurture it. The biggest myth is that our vote doesn’t matter.” Volume up for more useful and inspiring soundbites. #CoachNY

node.text:
Tag, you're it. Here's the 411 on our iconic hangtag. 

Story 33/80: Placed on every bag since 1972, the hangtag originally served as a place for our logo. (It has evolved to invoke our name by its shape alone.) In the '70s, we did a  campaign with the tagline, “It’s not a Coach bag without a Coach tag."

To celebrate our 80th, we're sharing 80 stories about you (and us). Tell us about your most memorable Coach moment below. #Coach80 #CoachNY

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Coach on July 18, 2021 tagging @laurenireland. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Imitation is the sincerest form of flattery. Just ask @summerfridays co-founder @laurenireland. 

Story 32/80 "I'll always remember taking the train to Chicago from my small hometown in Michigan to visit the ‘fancy’ shops. I was probably around nine, and my mom surprised me with a miniature coach purse to match my older sister’s. I was so proud holding that tiny purse, because it represented so much more than that — it held the adoration I always had for my sister.”

To celebrate our 80th, we're sharing 80 stories about you (and us). Tell us about your most memorable Coach moment below. #Coach80 #CoachNY

node.text:
Function, but make it fashion. That was big for #BonnieCashin, our first lead designer, when she created the iconic Duffle bag in 1971. 

Story 31/80: Inspired by "feed bags"— like those for horses— this slouchy, functional bag’s rich leather and easygoing attitude made it a hit. (In other words: all yay and no nay. 🐴) 

To celebrate our 80th, we're sharing 80 stories about you (and us). Tell us about your most memorable Coach moment below. #Coach80 #CoachNY

node.text:
Popular for a reason. Owner-designer of a sustainable vintage clothing collective @samimiro cemented her cool girl status early on. 👀

Story 30/80: "I remember I got my first Coach bag when I was 16. I saved up for months to get that bag and I remember how cool I was when I took it to school the next day. I was the envy of all my girls."

To celebrate our 80th, we're sharing 80 stories about you (and us). Tell us about your most memorable Coach moment below. #Coach80 #CoachNY

node.text:
When Coach 💚 is in your DNA. Case in point: singer, songwriter and dancer @babynezza. 

Story 26/80: "My mother devoted her life to my sister and me. She always found a way to spoil me, even when money was tight. My mother loved Coach, so I LOVED Coach. She would buy small items she found on sale (whether it was a wallet or small purse). Being able to share my Coach moments and bags with my mom is special."

To celebrate our 80th, we're sharing 80 stories about you (and us). Tell us about your most memorable Coach moment below. #Coach80 #CoachNY
